  Scene Extension

In this video, I'll show you how to expand the edges of your images using a process known as outcropping. For this video, we'll use Photoshop's new Generative Fill feature.

If you don't have the Photoshop Beta version installed on your computer. Do the following steps:

  • Go to the Creative Cloud App
  • Click 'Apps' in the top Menu
  • Click 'Beta Apps' from the Menu on the Left
  • Install Photoshop (Beta)

Note: Generative Fill replacements max out at 1024 pixels. If you are expanding beyond 1024 pixels and need full details and quality, create 1024-pixel boxes and slowly expand your frames. This video shows you the process if you are curious.
